  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2022-06-14",
    "date": "2022-09-06T21:48:13Z",
    "text": "First Opportunity for Information to Americans Act or the FOIA Fix Act\n\nThis bill bars certain foreign nationals and entities from obtaining U.S. government records under the Freedom of Information Act.\n\nThe bill specifically prohibits an agency from making records available to specified requesters, including an entity that is a subsidiary of an entity with a principal place of business or headquarters located in China, Russia, North Korea, Iran, Cuba, Syria, or Venezuela.\n\nFurther, the bill sets penalties for knowingly assisting, conspiring, or abetting a request for information on behalf of an individual or entity that is prohibited from receiving it."
  },
